	<text_base_description>From its perch atop Laurel Canyon, this four structure compound has commanding panoramic views. Adoringly nicknamed The Crown Jewel, 2114 Kew Drive has played host to a storied collection of Hollywood writers, directors, actors, novelists, and dancers. Lovingly restored, the property unfolds from the multiple outdoor seating areas, pool, and spa into the two-bedroom main home and pool house. The A-Frame guest house with kitchenette and the hillside bungalow has been named El Nido de Nestor after its long-time resident, Academy Award-winning cinematographer Nestor Almendros. Upon entry, the living space and dining room are framed by the landscaped exterior and downtown Los Angeles. The spacious kitchen, with an architectural ceiling, opens onto an outdoor dining patio. The primary suite, complete with sitting area, is outfitted with double doors leading directly to the pool and spa with magical starlight views.  </text_base_description>
